	<div class="info-hero-content">
		<p class="long-para info-heading">The Republic of China (Taiwan) was founded in 1912, making it the first democratic republic country in Asia. In 1949, the government moved to Taiwan and maintained jurisdiction over an area encompassing the islands of Taiwan, Penghu, Kinmen, Matsu, Dongsha, Zhongsha, and Nansha.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="content-container">
		<div class="content-block information-block">
			<div class="block-1" zum-waypoint="waypoints" down="first.on" offset="50%" ng-class="{'animated fadeInLeft': waypoints.first.on}">
				<h2>Location</h2>
				<p class="long-para">Taiwan's total land area is about 36,000 square kilometers (14,400 square miles). The land is shaped like a leaf. It lies off the southeastern coast, across the Taiwan Strait, of China. The island is located on the western edge of the Pacific Ocean. Japan is located in the north, Philippines in the south and Hong Kong to the west.</p>
			</div>
		</div>

