				<h2>Languages</h2>
				<p class="long-para">Mandarin is the official language used and spoken in Taiwan. However, many Benshengren speak a dialect of Taiwanese Hokkien (a variant of Minnan speech). There is also a Hakka ethnic group, which composes of about 15% of the population, that speak the Hakka language.</p>
