			<div class="block-4" zum-waypoint="waypoints" down="fourth.on" offset="50%" ng-class="{'animated fadeInLeft': waypoints.fourth.on}">
				<h2>Culture</h2>
				<p class="long-para">The Taiwanese culture is a hybrid mixture from the Taiwanese aborigines, Japanese culture, traditional Confucianist beliefs, Chinese culture and Western values. Culture has been a large part of political status debate on whether Taiwan is a descendant of Chinese culture or a distinct culture. In recent years, Taiwanese multiculturalism has been proposed with a redefined culture standpoint that is different than Asian cultures surrounding Taiwan. Throughout different cities and counties in Taiwan, you will see a radical culture change and language difference from the North (hybrid of Western and Chinese culture), South (hybrid of Japanese and Taiwanese aborigines), East (Taiwanese aborigines) and West (hybrid of Western and Taiwanese aborigines).</p>
			</div>
		</div>

